{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FgdWFCdKp3wWKzrBKYNJgx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**PLANNER SUMMARY**\n\n**Build strategy chosen:** `upstream_with_target_template`\n\n**Files written / modified:**\n\n| File | Action |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/moltnet/lzc-manifest.yml` | Created |\n| `apps/moltnet/lzc-build.yml` | Created |\n| `apps/moltnet/Dockerfile.template` | Created |\n| `apps/moltnet/README.md` | Created |\n| `apps/moltnet/icon.png` | Created (512×512 solid #3ddc84, 1.5 KB) |\n| `registry/repos/moltnet.json` | Created |\n| `registry/repos/index.json` | Updated (appended `moltnet.json`) |\n\n**Key decisions:**\n\n- **Port 8787** — upstream default (`MOLTNET_LISTEN_ADDR=:8787`), healthcheck at `GET /healthz`\n- **Login route: none** — moltnet's default auth mode is `none`; LazyCat session auth protects `/console/`. Agent attachment API (`/v1/`) is declared `public_path` so remote `moltnet node` daemons can connect with their own bearer tokens without being blocked by LazyCat auth.\n- **Data path:** `/lzcapp/var/data/moltnet` (host bind) → `/var/lib/moltnet` (container), SQLite at `/var/lib/moltnet/moltnet.db`. No `setup_script` needed — bind mount creates the host directory and the moltnet binary creates the DB file on first run.\n- **`MOLTNET_CONTAINER=true`** disables the in-binary auto-updater (correct for containerised deployment).\n- **Minimal config file** `/etc/Moltnet` with `version: moltnet.v1` baked into the image via `MOLTNET_CONFIG` env var — prevents startup failure when no `Moltnet` file exists in the working directory.\n- **Dockerfile.template risk note:** the `//go:embed` path for the built console is assumed to be `web/dist` relative to the module root. If the actual embed target is under a different package (e.g., `internal/transport/static`), the build will fail with a clear \"pattern: directory prefix does not exist\" error and the Dockerfile needs one additional `RUN cp -r web/dist <embed-target>` line.\n\n**No `waiting_for_human` blockers** — license is MIT, no GPU dependency, no external service required, no ambiguous auth setup."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":168,"cache_read_input_tokens":85551,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":168},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e426fc47-d3e7-4f68-b726-914dcf40f371","uuid":"8622e1ce-0d1a-45d4-a6cb-ce1b909b7fec"}
